  "description": "<p>The pinnacle of innovation that weighs less than 1L of water. The Parsec -18C Sleeping Bag uses premium fabrics and insulation to achieve an incredible warmth to weight ratio. The trim shape suits ski tourers and fast and light winter campers who count every gram. With the insulation distributed primarily on the top, it's efficient for cold nights at altitude. Reflective seams trap warmth to aid in heat retention and hydrophobic down manages dampness to maintain warmth through a range of conditions.</p><ul><li>800 fill-power Nikwax Hydrophobic Down is exceptionally warm and retains less moisture than traditional down</li><li>Down is certified to the Responsible Down Standard</li><li>Zoned insulation puts more fill on top, as your sleeping pad provides insulation, there is less down on the bottom of this bag</li><li>2 stretchy SynergyLink\u2122 connectors hold your pad in place under the bag</li><li>Cinchable hood features a heat-trapping draft collar</li><li>No-snag YKK zipper with full-length draft tube</li><li>Toe-asis\u2122 shaped toe box features an interior baffled pocket of insulation to warm your feet</li><li>External zip pocket houses a headlamp or contact lenses</li><li>Quilt loops let you customize your sleep system by attaching a Therm-a-rest quilt or blanket over top to add even more warmth</li><li>Includes a compression sack and storage sack</li></ul>",
